{"questionId":"25675","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the binomial expansion <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>7</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>35</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math> where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The third term in the expansion is the mean of the second term and the fourth term in&nbsp;the expansion.</p>\n<p>Find the possible values of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>21</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>35</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>21</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>35</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>correct quadratic equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\